- Locales refer to the language files 
- used to manage the text and translations displayed in your theme.
- multi-language store by customizing and translating all visible text ‚Äî including buttons, labels, messages, etc.

‚úÖ What Are Locales in Shopify?
- Locale files are JSON files located in the locales/ folder of your theme.
- Each file corresponds to a language (e.g., en.default.json, fr.default.json).

üìÅ Example: locales/en.default.json

{
  "general": {
    "welcome": "Welcome to our store!",
    "search": {
      "placeholder": "Search products..."
    }
  },
  "cart": {
    "empty": "Your cart is empty",
    "checkout": "Proceed to checkout"
  }
}

üëÄ How it Appears in Liquid:
<p>{{ 'general.welcome' | t }}</p>
<input placeholder="{{ 'general.search.placeholder' | t }}">
<p>{{ 'cart.empty' | t }}</p>


‚úÖ NOTE : If you want jn sceme code the create new file "en.default.schema.json" file in Locale folder and add code.

{
"sections": {
    "all": {
      "section_padding": {
        "top": {
          "label": "Main Title"
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

in sceme file,
 {
  "type": "text",
  "id": "content-title",
  "label": "t:sections.all.section_padding.top.label"
 },
